[{"id":"VR708799","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. The first figure shows an experiment with two cylinders of mass M placed on a rotating apparatus. Each of the blocks is a distance of r from the center of the apparatus. The second figure shows a graph of 2 lines in the gridded plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “r squared in square meters,” and the numbers 0.00 through 0.20, in increments of 0.05, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Rotational Inertia in kilogram square meters,” and the numbers 0.00 through 0.05, in increments of 0.01, are indicated. The first line is labeled “Unknown Mass” and it starts at 0.01 on the vertical axis and it moves up and to the right diagonally passing through coordinates 0.05 comma 0.02, 0.10 comma 0.03, 0.15 comma 0.04, and ends at 0.20 comma 0.05. The second line is labeled “Mass M” and it also begins at 0.01 on the vertical axis and the line moves up and to the right passing through the coordinates 0.10 comma 0.02 and ends at coordinates 0.20 comma 0.03.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR708799.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two identical cylinders of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span> are attached to a rotating apparatus at equal distances <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> from the rotation axis, as shown in the figure. The rotational inertia <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l\"><math alttext=\"l\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> of the apparatus-cylinders system is experimentally determined for multiple values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span>. The solid line in the graph shows the best-fit line for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l\"><math alttext=\"l\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> as a function of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r squared\"><math alttext=\"r squared\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></span></span> for the identical cylinders with mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span>. The experiment is then repeated for two other identical cylinders of unknown mass. The dashed line in the graph shows the best-fit line for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l\"><math alttext=\"l\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> as a function of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r squared\"><math alttext=\"r squared\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></span></span> for the cylinders of unknown mass. Based on the graph, what is the unknown mass in terms of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR708799_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction M over 4\"><math alttext=\"the fraction M over 4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction M over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction M over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 M\"><math alttext=\"2 M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 M\"><math alttext=\"4 M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mi>M</mi></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]